00218 M_hppa_eval_type (M_Type type, M_Type ntype)
00219 {
00220   switch (type->type)
00221     {
00222     case M_TYPE_VOID:
00223       M_void (ntype);
00224       return (-1);              /* can not be evaluated */
00225     case M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR:
00226     case M_TYPE_CHAR:
00227     case M_TYPE_SHORT:
00228     case M_TYPE_BLOCK:
00229     case M_TYPE_INT:
00230     case M_TYPE_BIT_LONG:
00231     case M_TYPE_LONG:
00232     case M_TYPE_POINTER:
00233       /* the starting address of array is used */
00234       M_int (ntype, type->unsign);
00235       return (M_TYPE_INT);
00236     case M_TYPE_FLOAT:
00237       M_float (ntype, type->unsign);
00238       return (M_TYPE_FLOAT);
00239     case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:
00240       M_double (ntype, type->unsign);
00241       return (M_TYPE_DOUBLE);
00242     case M_TYPE_UNION:
00243     case M_TYPE_STRUCT:
00244       *ntype = *type;
00245       return type->type;
00246     default:
00247       return (-1);
00248     }

00431 {
00432   int i, max;
00433   max = 0;
00434   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00435     {
00436       int aln = type[i].align;
00437       if (aln > max)
00438         max = aln;

00440   /*
00441    *  align to at least byte boundary.

00444     max = M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR;
00445 
00446   return max;

00449 int
00450 M_hppa_union_size (int n, _M_Type * type)
00451 {
00452   int i, aln, max_size, max_align;
00453 
00454   max_size = 0;
00455   max_align = 0;
00456   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00457     {
00458       int size;
00459       size = type[i].size;
00460       if (size > max_size)
00461         max_size = size;
00462       aln = type[i].align;
00463       if (aln > max_align)
00464         max_align = aln;
00465     }
00466   /*
00467    *  align to at least byte boundary.
00468    */
00469   if (max_align < M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR)
00470     max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR;
00471 
00472   /* need to increment to the max. align for future array extension */
00473   i = max_size % max_align;
00474   if (i != 0)
00475     max_size += (max_align - i);
00476 
00477   return max_size;
00478 }

00483 void
00484 M_hppa_struct_layout (int n, _M_Type * type, int *base, int *bit_offset)
00485 {
00486   int i, offset;
00487   int mod, size, align, mod_word, mod_type;
00488 
00489   offset = 0;                   /* assume initially aligned */
00490   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00491     {
00492       size = type[i].size;
00493       align = type[i].align;
00494       M_assert ((size != 0) && (align != 0),
00495                 "M_struct_layout: void is not allowed in structure");
00496       /*
00497        *  need to treat bit fields specially.
00498        *  keep them in a word when possible.
00499        */
00500       mod_word = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00501       if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00502         {
00503           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00504             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00505           else
00506             {
00507               mod_type = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_CHAR;
00508               if ((mod_type + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_CHAR)
00509                 {
00510                   /* fprintf(stdout,"Changing bit char to bit short\n"); */
00511                   type[i].type = M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT;
00512                 }
00513             }
00514         }
00515       if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00516         {
00517           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00518             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00519           else
00520             {
00521               mod_type = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_SHORT;
00522               if ((mod_type + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_SHORT)
00523                 {
00524                   /* fprintf(stdout,"Changing bit short to bit long\n"); */
00525                   type[i].type = M_TYPE_BIT_LONG;
00526                 }
00527             }
00528         }
00529       else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00530         {
00531           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00532             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00533         }
00534 
00535       mod = offset % align;     /* align to what the field */
00536       if (mod != 0)             /* needs to start from */
00537         offset += (align - mod);
00538 
00539       if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00540         {
00541           int mod = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00542 
00543           bit_offset[i] = offset - mod + (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00544           base[i] = offset & (~(M_HPPA_SIZE_CHAR - 1));
00545 #if 0
00546           fprintf (stderr, "type = %d, base = %d, bit_offset = %d\n",
00547                    type[i].type, base[i], bit_offset[i]);
00548 #endif
00549         }
00550       else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00551         {
00552           int mod = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00553 
00554           bit_offset[i] = offset - mod + (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00555           base[i] = offset & (~(M_HPPA_SIZE_SHORT - 1));
00556 #if 0
00557           fprintf (stderr, "type = %d, base = %d, bit_offset = %d\n",
00558                    type[i].type, base[i], bit_offset[i]);
00559 #endif
00560         }
00561       else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00562         {
00563           int mod = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00564 
00565           bit_offset[i] = offset - mod + (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00566           base[i] = offset & (~(M_HPPA_SIZE_LONG - 1));
00567 #if 0
00568           fprintf (stderr, "type = %d, base = %d, bit_offset = %d\n",
00569                    type[i].type, base[i], bit_offset[i]);
00570 #endif
00571         }
00572       else
00573         {
00574           base[i] = offset;
00575           bit_offset[i] = 0;
00576 #if 0
00577           fprintf (stderr, "type = %d, base = %d, bit_offset = %d\n",
00578                    type[i].type, base[i], bit_offset[i]);
00579 #endif
00580 
00581         }
00582 
00583       offset += size;           /* allocate space */
00584     }
00585 }

00606 int
00607 M_hppa_struct_size (int n, _M_Type * type, int struct_align)
00608 {
00609   int i, offset;
00610   int mod, size, align, max_align, mod_word;
00611   offset = 0;                   /* assume initially aligned */
00612   max_align = struct_align;
00613   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00614     {
00615       size = type[i].size;
00616       align = type[i].align;
00617       M_assert ((size != 0) && (align != 0),
00618                 "M_struct_layout: void is not allowed in structure");
00619       if (align > max_align)
00620         max_align = align;
00621       /*
00622        *  need to treat bit fields specially.
00623        *  keep them in a word when possible.
00624        */
00625       mod_word = offset % M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00626       if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00627         {
00628           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00629             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00630           if (M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR > max_align)
00631             max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR;
00632         }
00633       else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00634         {
00635           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00636             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00637           if (M_HPPA_ALIGN_SHORT > max_align)
00638             max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_SHORT;
00639         }
00640       else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00641         {
00642           if ((mod_word + size) > M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00643             offset += (M_HPPA_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00644           if (M_HPPA_ALIGN_LONG > max_align)
00645             max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_LONG;
00646         }
00647       mod = offset % align;     /* align to what the field */
00648       if (mod != 0)             /* needs to start from */
00649         offset += (align - mod);
00650 
00651       offset += size;
00652     }
00653   /*
00654    * align to at least byte boundary.
00655    */
00656   if (max_align < M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR)
00657     max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_CHAR;
00658   /* enforce max. alignment */
00659   mod = offset % max_align;
00660   if (mod != 0)
00661     offset += (max_align - mod);
00662   return offset;
00663 }

00717 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
00718 int
00719 M_hppa_fnvar_layout (int n, _M_Type * type, long int *offset, int *mode,
00720                      int *reg, int *paddr, char **macro,
00721                      int *su_sreg, int *su_ereg,
00722                      int *pcount, int is_st, int purpose)
00723                                         /* need to return structure */
00724 {
00725   int i, max_align, off, rg;
00726   int size, align, mod, tp;
00727 
00728 
00729   switch (purpose)
00730     {
00731     case M_GET_FNVAR:
00732       *macro = "$IP";
00733       break;
00734     case M_PUT_FNVAR:
00735       *macro = "$OP";
00736       break;
00737     case M_DONT_CARE_FNVAR:
00738     default:
00739       M_assert (0, "M_fnvar_layout: unknown purpose");
00740     }
00741 
00742   max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_MAX;
00743   rg = 0;
00744   off = 0;
00745 
00746   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00747     {
00748       tp = type[i].type;
00749       switch (tp)
00750         {
00751         case M_TYPE_CHAR:
00752         case M_TYPE_SHORT:
00753         case M_TYPE_INT:
00754         case M_TYPE_LONG:
00755         case M_TYPE_POINTER:
00756           if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00757             {
00758               mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00759               reg[i] = (rg)++ + M_HPPA_INT_BASE;
00760             }
00761           else
00762             {
00763               mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00764               reg[i] = -1;
00765             }
00766           break;
00767 
00768         case M_TYPE_FLOAT:
00769           if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00770             {
00771               mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00772               reg[i] = (rg)++ + M_HPPA_FLT_BASE;
00773             }
00774           else
00775             {
00776               mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00777               reg[i] = -1;
00778             }
00779           break;
00780 
00781         case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:
00782           if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00783             {
00784               if (rg == 0 || rg == 2)
00785                 {
00786                   mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00787                   reg[i] = rg + 1 + M_HPPA_FLT_BASE;
00788                   rg += 2;
00789                 }
00790               else if (rg == 1)
00791                 {
00792                   mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00793                   reg[i] = 3 + M_HPPA_FLT_BASE;
00794                   rg += 3;
00795                 }
00796               else
00797                 {
00798                   mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00799                   reg[i] = -1;
00800                   rg += 3;      /* Rest of parms go in memory -JCG 11/16/98 */
00801                 }
00802             }
00803           else
00804             {
00805               mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00806               reg[i] = -1;
00807             }
00808           break;
00809 
00810         case M_TYPE_UNION:
00811         case M_TYPE_STRUCT:
00812           size = type[i].size;
00813           if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00814             {
00815               printf ("hppa: M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER\n");
00816               mode[i] = M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER;
00817               reg[i] = (rg)++ + M_HPPA_INT_BASE;
00818             }
00819           else
00820             {
00821               if (size <= M_HPPA_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX)
00822                 {
00823                   printf ("hppa: M_THRU_MEMORY\n");
00824                   mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00825                 }
00826               else
00827                 {
00828                   printf ("hppa:  M_INDIRECT_THRU_MEMORY\n");
00829                   mode[i] = M_INDIRECT_THRU_MEMORY;
00830                 }
00831               reg[i] = -1;
00832             }
00833           break;
00834 #if 0
00835 /* IMPACT does not allow passing of structures via registers, therefore */
00836 /* where structures are concerned, HP's calling convention is ignored   */
00837           size = type[i].size;
00838           if (size <= M_HPPA_SIZE_INT)
00839             {
00840               if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00841                 {
00842                   mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00843                   reg[i] = (rg)++ + M_HPPA_INT_BASE;
00844                 }
00845               else
00846                 {
00847                   mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00848                   reg[i] = -1;
00849                 }
00850             }
00851           else if (size <= M_HPPA_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX)
00852             {
00853               if ((rg == 0) || (rg == 2))
00854                 {
00855                   mode[i] = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00856                   reg[i] = rg + M_HPPA_INT_BASE;
00857                   rg += 2;
00858                 }
00859               else
00860                 {
00861                   mode[i] = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00862                   reg[i] = -1;
00863                 }
00864               /*
00865                  else
00866                  {
00867                  if (rg < M_HPPA_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00868                  {
00869                  mode[i] = M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER;
00870                  reg[i] = (rg)++ + M_HPPA_INT_BASE;
00871                  }
00872                  else
00873                  {
00874                  mode[i] = M_INDIRECT_THRU_MEMORY;
00875                  reg[i] = -1;
00876                  }
00877                  }
00878                */
00879             }
00880           break;
00881 #endif
00882         default:
00883           M_assert (0, "M_fnvar_layout: argument is not promoted");
00884         }
00885 
00886       /* note, the method of calculating offsets may seem strange, but */
00887       /* the PA convention has the stack growing towards high memory   */
00888       /* and the parameters are referenced back from the $sp, with the */
00889       /* first parameter being closest to the stack pointer            */
00890       size = type[i].size;
00891       align = type[i].align;
00892 
00893       if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_UNION || type[i].type == M_TYPE_STRUCT)
00894         {
00895           /* make sure correct size and alignment is used for struct/union */
00896           /* passed indirectly thru registers                              */
00897           /* if IMPACT allowed structures to be passed via registers, this */
00898           /* would not have to be done                                     */
00899           if (mode[i] == M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER)
00900             {
00901               size = M_HPPA_SIZE_INT;
00902               align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_INT;
00903             }
00904         }
00905       if (align >= M_HPPA_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX && type[i].type != M_TYPE_DOUBLE)
00906         /* anything larger than a 64-bit structure is passed */
00907         /* indirectly thru memory                            */
00908         align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_INT;
00909       else if (align < M_HPPA_ALIGN_INT)
00910         /* anything smaller that 32-bits is passed as 32-bits */
00911         align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_INT;
00912 
00913       mod = off % align;
00914 
00915       /* place the offset pointer to the boundary of the appropriate */
00916       /* data size                                                   */
00917       if (mod != 0)
00918         off += (align - mod);
00919 
00920       /* now increment the offset to point to the actual location    */
00921       /* for this parameter                                          */
00922       off += size;
00923 
00924       offset[i] = -off;
00925     }
00926 
00927   /* The param section must be at least certain size.
00928    * This is the backing store for the parameter regs. */
00929   if (off < MIN_PARAM_SIZE)
00930     off = MIN_PARAM_SIZE;
00931 
00932   /* now for the body of the structures... small ones first. */
00933   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00934     {
00935       tp = type[i].type;
00936 
00937       size = type[i].size;
00938 
00939       if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
00940            (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) && (size <= M_HPPA_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
00941         {
00942 
00943           align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_MAX;     /* must align to a double boundry */
00944 
00945           mod = off % align;
00946 
00947           if (mod != 0)
00948             off += (align - mod);
00949 
00950           off += size;
00951 
00952           printf ("1 size %d off %d", size, off);
00953           paddr[i] = -off;
00954           printf ("1 paddr[%d] = %d\n", i, paddr[i]);
00955         }
00956     }
00957 
00958   /* now large ones */
00959   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00960     {
00961       tp = type[i].type;
00962 
00963       size = type[i].size;
00964 
00965       if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
00966            (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) && (size > M_HPPA_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
00967         {
00968 
00969           align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_MAX;     /* must align to a double boundry */
00970 
00971           mod = off % align;
00972 
00973           if (mod != 0)
00974             off += (align - mod);
00975 
00976           off += size;
00977 
00978           printf ("2 size %d off %d", size, off);
00979           paddr[i] = -off;
00980           printf ("2 paddr[%d] = %d\n", i, paddr[i]);
00981         }
00982     }
00983 
00984   *pcount = rg;
00985   return off;                   /* the total size needed */
00986 }

00988 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
00989 int
00990 M_hppa_lvar_layout (int n, _M_Type * type, long int *offset,
00991                     char **base_macro)
00992 {
00993   int i, max_align, off;
00994   int size, align, mod, tp;
00995   /*
00996    *  the LOCAL section must be max. aligned initially
00997    */
00998   max_align = M_HPPA_ALIGN_MAX;
00999   off = 0;
01000   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
01001     {
01002       tp = type[i].type;
01003       if (tp == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
01004         {
01005           M_assert (0, "M_lvar_layout: bit field not allowed");
01006         }
01007       if (tp == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
01008         {
01009           M_assert (0, "M_lvar_layout: bit field not allowed");
01010         }
01011       size = type[i].size;
01012       align = type[i].align;
01013       mod = off % align;
01014       if (mod != 0)
01015         off += (align - mod);
01016       off += size;
01017 
01018       offset[i] = -off;
01019     }
01020 
01021   /* the local section must be max. aligned */
01022   mod = off % max_align;
01023   if (mod != 0)
01024     off += (max_align - mod);
01025   /*
01026    *  Local variables are relative to $LV
01027    */
01028   *base_macro = "$LV";
01029   return off;                   /* the total size needed */
01030 }

01057 /* Format for hppa is: _$%sM_JUMPTBL_BASE_NAME%d, where %s is the func name */
01058 int
01059 M_hppa_is_jumptbl_label (char *label, char *fn, int *tbl_id)
01060 {
01061   char *ptr;
01062   int label_len, fn_len, base_len;
01063 
01064   /* Check the prefix */
01065   if (strncmp (label, "_$", 2))
01066     return (0);
01067 
01068   /* Some length checks, to make sure we dont step outside array */
01069   label_len = strlen (label);
01070   fn_len = strlen (fn);
01071   base_len = strlen (M_JUMPTBL_BASE_NAME);
01072   if (label_len <= (2 + fn_len + base_len))
01073     return (0);
01074 
01075   /* Check that fn is correct */
01076   ptr = label;
01077   ptr += 2;
01078   if (strncmp (ptr, fn, fn_len))
01079     return (0);
01080 
01081   /* Check that jumptbl base name is correct */
01082   ptr += fn_len;
01083   if (strncmp (ptr, M_JUMPTBL_BASE_NAME, base_len))
01084     return (0);
01085 
01086   /* Get the id */
01087   ptr += base_len;
01088   return (sscanf (ptr, "%d", tbl_id) == 1);
01089 }

01385 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
01386 int
01387 M_hppa_dataflow_macro (int id)
01388 {
01389   switch (M_model)
01390     {
01391     case M_HP_PA_1_0:
01392     case M_HP_PA_1_1:
01393     case M_HP_PA_7100:
01394     case M_HP_PA_X:
01395     case M_HP_PLAYDOH_LCODE:
01396     case M_HP_PLAYDOH_MCODE:
01397       if (id >= HPPA_MAC_PLAYDOH_GPR && id <= HPPA_MAC_LAST)
01398         return 0;
01399       else
01400         return ((id >= L_MAC_P0 && id <= L_MAC_P64) || (id >= L_MAC_LAST));
01401     default:
01402       M_assert (0, "M_hppa_dataflow_macro:  Illegal model specified!");
01403       return (0);
01404     }
01405 }
01406 
01407 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
01408 int
01409 M_hppa_subroutine_call (int opc)
01410 {
01411   switch (M_model)
01412     {
01413     case M_HP_PA_1_0:
01414       return ((opc == Lop_JSR) || (opc == Lop_JSR_FS) ||
01415               (opc == Lop_MUL) || (opc == Lop_MUL_U) ||
01416               (opc == Lop_DIV) || (opc == Lop_DIV_U) ||
01417               (opc == Lop_REM) || (opc == Lop_REM_U));
01418     case M_HP_PA_1_1:
01419     case M_HP_PA_7100:
01420     case M_HP_PA_X:
01421     case M_HP_PLAYDOH_LCODE:
01422     case M_HP_PLAYDOH_MCODE:
01423       return ((opc == Lop_JSR)
01424               || (opc ==
01425                   Lop_JSR_FS)
01426               || (opc ==
01427                   Lop_MUL)
01428               || (opc ==
01429                   Lop_MUL_U)
01430               || (opc ==
01431                   Lop_DIV)
01432               || (opc == Lop_DIV_U) || (opc == Lop_REM) || (opc == Lop_REM_U));
01433     default:
01434       M_assert (0, "M_hppa_subroutine_call:  Illegal model specified!");
01435       return (0);
01436     }
01437 }

02155 /*
02156  * Returns the number of machine instructions required to implement the
02157  * specified oper in the best case.  It is assumed that this is for
02158  * supported instructions.  A call to M_oper_supported_in_arch should be
02159  * made for abnormal instructions.
02160  */
02161 
02162 int
02163 M_num_oper_required_for_hppa (L_Oper * oper, char *name)
02164 {
02165 #define has_label_operand(a)    ((a->src[0]->type == L_OPERAND_LABEL)||\
02166                                  (a->src[1]->type == L_OPERAND_LABEL))
02167 
02168 #define indexed_memory_op(a)    ((a->src[0]->type == L_OPERAND_REGISTER)&&\
02169                                  (a->src[1]->type == L_OPERAND_REGISTER))
02170 
02171 #define non_zero_offset(a)      ((!((a->src[1]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED)&&\
02172                                    ((a->src[1]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)))||\
02173                                  (a->src[1]->value.i != 0))
02174 
02175 #define short_int_inc(a,b)      ((a->src[b]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED)&&\
02176                                  ((a->src[b]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\
02177                                  (a->src[b]->value.i >= -0x10) &&\
02178                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0x10))
02179 #define long_pos_int_inc(a,b)   ((a->src[b]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED)&&\
02180                                  ((a->src[b]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\
02181                                  (a->src[b]->value.i > 0) && \
02182                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0x2000))
02183 #define long_neg_int_inc(a,b)   ((a->src[b]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED)&&\
02184                                  ((a->src[b]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\
02185                                  (a->src[b]->value.i >= -0x2000) && \
02186                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0))
02187 #define register_inc(a,b)        (a->src[b]->type == L_OPERAND_REGISTER)
02188 
02189   switch (oper->opc)
02190     {
02191     case Lop_ST_C:
02192     case Lop_ST_C2:
02193     case Lop_ST_I:
02194       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || has_label_operand (oper))
02195         return (2);
02196       else
02197         return (1);
02198 
02199     case Lop_LD_UC:
02200     case Lop_LD_C:
02201     case Lop_LD_UC2:
02202     case Lop_LD_C2:
02203     case Lop_LD_I:
02204       if (has_label_operand (oper))
02205         return (2);
02206       else
02207         return (1);
02208 
02209     case Lop_ST_F:
02210     case Lop_ST_F2:
02211       if (has_label_operand (oper))
02212         return (2);
02213       else
02214         return (1);
02215 
02216     case Lop_LD_F:
02217     case Lop_LD_F2:
02218       if (has_label_operand (oper))
02219         return (2);
02220       else
02221         return (1);
02222 
02223     case Lop_LD_PRE_UC:
02224     case Lop_LD_PRE_C:
02225     case Lop_LD_PRE_UC2:
02226     case Lop_LD_PRE_C2:
02227     case Lop_LD_PRE_I:
02228       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
02229         return (2);
02230       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2) || long_neg_int_inc (oper, 2))
02231         return (1);
02232       else
02233         return (2);
02234 
02235     case Lop_ST_PRE_C:
02236     case Lop_ST_PRE_C2:
02237     case Lop_ST_PRE_I:
02238       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
02239         return (2);
02240       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 3) || long_neg_int_inc (oper, 3))
02241         return (1);
02242       else
02243         return (2);
02244 
02245     case Lop_LD_POST_UC:
02246     case Lop_LD_POST_C:
02247     case Lop_LD_POST_UC2:
02248     case Lop_LD_POST_C2:
02249     case Lop_LD_POST_I:
02250       if (non_zero_offset (oper))
02251         return (2);
02252       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2) ||
02253                long_pos_int_inc (oper, 2) || register_inc (oper, 2))
02254         return (1);
02255       else
02256         return (2);
02257 
02258     case Lop_ST_POST_C:
02259     case Lop_ST_POST_C2:
02260     case Lop_ST_POST_I:
02261       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
02262         return (2);
02263       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 3) || long_pos_int_inc (oper, 3))
02264         return (1);
02265       else
02266         return (2);
02267 
02268     case Lop_LD_PRE_F:
02269     case Lop_LD_PRE_F2:
02270       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
02271         return (2);
02272       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2))
02273         return (1);
02274       else
02275         return (2);
02276 
02277     case Lop_ST_PRE_F:
02278     case Lop_ST_PRE_F2:
02279       if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
02280         return (2);
02281       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 3))
02282         return (1);
02283       else
02284         return (2);
02285 
02286     case Lop_LD_POST_F:
02287     case Lop_LD_POST_F2:
02288       if (non_zero_offset (oper))
02289         return (2);
02290       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2) || register_inc (oper, 2))
02291         return (1);
02292       else
02293         return (2);
02294     case Lop_ST_POST_F:
02295     case Lop_ST_POST_F2:
02296       if (non_zero_offset (oper))
02297         return (2);
02298       else if (short_int_inc (oper, 3) || register_inc (oper, 3))
02299         return (1);
02300       else
02301         return (2);
02302 
02303     case Lop_PREF_LD:
02304       if (has_label_operand (oper))
02305         return (2);
02306       else
02307         return (1);
02308 
02309     default:
02310       return (1);
02311     }

02386 int
02387 M_conflicting_operands_hppa (L_Operand * operand,
02388                              L_Operand ** conflict_array, int len,
02389                              int prepass)
02390 {
02391   int right = 0, left = 0;
02392 
02393   if (prepass && (!L_is_macro (operand)))
02394     {
02395       conflict_array[0] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02396       return (1);
02397     }
02398   if (L_is_macro (operand))
02399     {
02400       switch (operand->value.mac)
02401         {
02402         case L_MAC_SP:
02403         case HPPA_MAC_TRUE_SP:
02404         case L_MAC_SAFE_MEM:
02405           conflict_array[0] =
02406             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SP, L_CTYPE_INT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
02407           conflict_array[1] =
02408             L_new_macro_operand (HPPA_MAC_TRUE_SP, L_CTYPE_INT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
02409           conflict_array[2] =
02410             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SAFE_MEM, L_CTYPE_INT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
02411           return (3);
02412         case L_MAC_P4:
02413         case L_MAC_P5:
02414         case L_MAC_P6:
02415         case L_MAC_P7:
02416           left = operand->value.mac;
02417           right = left + 4;
02418           break;
02419         case L_MAC_P8:
02420         case L_MAC_P9:
02421         case L_MAC_P10:
02422         case L_MAC_P11:
02423           right = operand->value.mac;
02424           left = right - 4;
02425           break;
02426         default:
02427           conflict_array[0] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02428           return (1);
02429         }
02430     }
02431   else if (L_is_reg (operand))
02432     {
02433       if (operand->value.r - MAX_INT_NAME > 0)
02434         {                       /* floating point register */
02435           if (operand->value.r - MAX_INT_NAME - 32 > 0)
02436             {
02437               /* right side of a floating point register */
02438               right = operand->value.r;
02439               left = operand->value.r - 32;
02440             }
02441           else
02442             {
02443               /* left side of a floating point register */
02444               left = operand->value.r;
02445               right = operand->value.r + 32;
02446             }
02447         }
02448       else
02449         {                       /* integer register */
02450           conflict_array[0] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02451           return (1);
02452         }
02453     }
02454   else
02455     M_assert (0, "Lhppa_conflicting_operands: unsupported operand type");
02456 
02457   if (L_is_ctype_dbl (operand))
02458     {
02459       /* Set up conflicting double register */
02460       conflict_array[0] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02461       conflict_array[0]->value.r = left;
02462 
02463       /* Set up conflicting float register */
02464       conflict_array[1] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02465       conflict_array[1]->ctype = L_CTYPE_FLOAT;
02466       conflict_array[1]->value.r = left;
02467 
02468       conflict_array[2] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02469       conflict_array[2]->ctype = L_CTYPE_FLOAT;
02470       conflict_array[2]->value.r = right;
02471       return (3);
02472     }
02473   else if (L_is_ctype_flt (operand))
02474     {
02475       /* Set up conflicting double register */
02476       conflict_array[0] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02477       conflict_array[0]->ctype = L_CTYPE_DOUBLE;
02478       conflict_array[0]->value.r = left;
02479 
02480       /* Set up conflicting double register */
02481       conflict_array[1] = L_copy_operand (operand);
02482       return (2);
02483     }
02484   else
02485     {
02486       M_assert (0, "Lhppa_conflicting_operands: unsupported operand type");
